19
00:01:38,331 --> 00:01:39,889
Ross.
罗斯

20
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:42,860
Could I have a scone, please?
阿甘，给我一个英式松饼

21
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:46,130
-Want to hear some good news? -ls somebody else gonna give it to us?
想听好消息吗？ 有别人要说吗？ 

22
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:49,430
Because you certainly don't seem like you have any.
你不像有好消息的样子

23
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,600
No,I do. Someone I know is getting married.
不，我有 我认识的某人要结婚了

24
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:56,900
Weddings are happy occasions. Oh,it's my ex-wife,Emily!
婚礼是最开心的场合 对了，那人是我的前妻艾蜜莉

26
00:01:58,850 --> 00:01:59,840
Sorry,man.
什么？ 怎么会这样

27
00:02:00,050 --> 00:02:01,850
-Here's your scone. -Thanks.
你的英式松饼 谢谢

29
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:07,520
Stupid British snack food!
什么白痴英国点心！

30
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:11,820
Did they teach you that in anger management class?
那是情绪管理课教的吗？

31
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,230
You know what might help you deal with it? Think it this way.
我有个办法，你就这么想

32
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,830
You two are in the past. You can't be mad about the past.
你和艾蜜莉已经过去了 你不能对过去的事生气

33
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:23,940
Are you still mad about, you know, the Louisiana Purchase?
你还气我们跟法国买土地吗？

34
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,270
Nobody's mad about that.
菲比，没有人在气那个

35
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:30,200
Exactly! Because it's in the past.
没错，因为已经过去了

36
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:35,210
Anybody going to eat that?
那个有人要吃吗？

37
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:43,250
Look at us all dressed up for the party. What are we celebrating?
我们盛装参加公司宴会耶 是在庆祝什么？ 

38
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:46,290
We had a lot of liquor left over from Christmas.
圣诞晚会剩了不少酒

39
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:51,890
Our friends aren't here. We can be a real couple. We don't have to hide.
真好，这里没有我们的朋友 我们可以公开，不必躲躲藏藏

40
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:53,960
I know. I can do this.
没错，我可以这样

41
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,700
And I can do this.
而我可以这样

42
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:00,240
We can't do that.
我们不能那样

43
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,970
Hey,Bing!
宾

44
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:07,900
Who's the pretty lady, and what is she doing with you?
这位美女是谁 怎么跟你在一起？

45
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,750
I asked myself that very question,sir. This is Monica.
我也这样问自己 这是摩妮卡

46
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:12,910
My boss,Doug.
我上司道格

47
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,750
-This is Monica. -Hi.
道格，这是摩妮卡

48
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,580
-This is my wife,Kara. -Nice to meet you.
幸会 这是我老婆卡拉 很高兴认识你… 宾

50
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,400
Did you hear about the new law firm working for us?
公司找了新法律顾问公司 是吗？

51
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,530
Dickem,Stickem & Run.
杜塔、片达、豪伊事务所 （堵他，骗他，好耶）

52
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:31,400
Let's go drink our body weight.
我们去喝个痛快

53
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,340
What was that? What？
那是什么？ 什么？

54
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:36,670
That noise you made?
你刚才发出的声音 

55
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,140
Oh,my work laugh.
那是我的工作笑

56
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,870
Your work laugh?
你的工作笑？

57
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:44,020
If you're going to survive this party, come up with one too.
相信我，想熬过这场派对 你也得编出一个来

58
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:46,040
All right. Check me out.
好，看我的 好

59
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:50,420
He says,"$30,Father. Same as in town."
…30块钱，跟城里一样

60
00:03:57,930 --> 00:04:00,530
Everybody at work loved you last night.
昨晚公司的人都好喜欢你

61
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,940
And they like me more just because I was with you.
真的？ 而且他们因为你而更喜欢我

62
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:07,110
You repaired the damage from when they met Joey.
你弥补了不少乔伊造成的伤害

63
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:12,500
Doug wants to play tennis. He never talks to me outside of work.
道格还找我们打网球 他出了公司还没理过我

64
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:15,050
Except for that time at that strip club.
除了在脱衣舞夜总会那次

65
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:19,080
Strip church.
脱衣舞教堂

66
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:24,020
-I'll go find a racket. -I thought you had one.
我要去找一支球拍 你不是有一支？

67
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:28,360
I used to,but then Joey thought it'd be fun to go hit rocks...
后来被乔伊拿去中央公园 对着石头打…

68
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,190
...at bigger rocks.
大石头

69
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:33,360
Do you have a tennis racket?
瑞秋，你有网球拍吗？

70
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:36,370
I lent it to Joey,and I've never gotten it back.
我借给乔伊就没拿回来过

71
00:04:37,470 --> 00:04:38,630
Good luck with that.
祝你好运

72
00:04:43,310 --> 00:04:44,400
What's up?
你好吗？

73
00:04:44,650 --> 00:04:47,210
Why are you here? I thought you had inventory.
你怎么来了？今天不是要盘点

74
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:49,820
I do,but I decided I'd take a long lunch...
没错，但我决定午休久一点 

75
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,640
...and spend some time with my friend Monica.
陪陪我的朋友摩妮卡

76
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:56,420
You know,I feel like we don't talk anymore.
我们现在都不谈心了

77
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:57,960
How are you?
你好吗？

78
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,820
What is new with you?
有什么新变化？

79
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:05,600
Not much. Work's good.
不多，工作很顺利

80
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,960
We don't have to talk about work. Talk about anything.
我们不必聊工作 什么都可以聊

81
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,542
好吧…

82
00:05:11,970 --> 00:05:13,500
You know what?
这样吧

83
00:05:14,410 --> 00:05:15,930
Let's talk about relationships.
我们来聊感情的事

84
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:17,480
What's going on?
好，你最近怎样？

85
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,140
Nothing.
没人追

86
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:21,100
You go.
该你

87
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:25,950
There was this guy at the bank that I thought was cute.
我原本觉得银行有一个人很帅 

88
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:27,640
But I don't anymore.
现在不觉得了

89
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:30,580
That's juicy.
真精彩

90
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:35,120
You know what? I actually do have a lot of work to do.
不过我确实很忙 

91
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:38,700
You're sure there's just not anything else?
你确定没别的了？

92
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:42,490
I'm sure. Is there something you want to talk to me about?
确定，你有什么事想说吗？ 

93
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,930
No!
没有

95
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:50,500
If there was,I wouldn't tell you.
好吧，有也不告诉你

96
00:05:58,450 --> 00:05:59,780
Then what happened?
好，然后呢？

97
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,860
You'll get your turn.
待会才轮到你

98
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:10,830
-Hey,Phoebe. What's going on? -Nothing.
菲比，在干什么？ 没什么

99
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,460
This is not over.
待会再继续

100
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:15,630
No,no,no!
糟糕 怎么了？

101
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:19,310
I was up all night writing this nasty letter to Emily.
我熬了一整晚写信骂艾蜜莉

102
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:22,370
It was perfect, and now it's all covered in....
原本写得很好，现在沾满了…

103
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:24,240
Actually,thanks!
谢了

104
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:27,550
All right! Ready to go to the movies?
可以去看电影了吗？

105
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,850
Actually,I think I'll skip it.
我想我不去了

106
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:31,210
Really?
你不去？

107
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:34,580
I'll read my book. I just want to be alone right now.
对，我要留下来看书 我现在只想静一静

109
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:36,390
Sure you don't want to?
你真的不去？

110
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:40,680
Tom Hanks,Meg Ryan. They get mail and stuff.
汤姆汉克斯，梅格莱恩 写信什么的

111
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,860
That's okay,Joe.
我还是不去了

112
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,690
Let's go, Phoebe.
好吧，菲比我们走

113
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:50,175
好恶

114
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:55,972
宾

115
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:02,880
Game!
赢了

116
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:08,250
I got to tell you,that partner of yours is a real tiger.
说真的，你的搭档真是快狠准

117
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,220
Are you all right?
你还好吗？

118
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:15,900
We'll just get a little sip of water.
我们喝口水

119
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:20,430
Am I on fire today or what?
我今天很猛吧？

120
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:24,760
Those birds are browned, basted and ready to be carved.
那两支肉鸡已经烤好 等着被切来吃了

121
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,400
Okay,easy,Martina.
别激动，网球名将

122
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:31,700
I think we should let them win the next game.
我觉得下一场应该让他们赢

123
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:34,880
I'm sorry,I don't understand what you just said.
对不起，你刚说的话我听不懂

124
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:37,280
Let them win one.
让他们赢一场

125
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:41,650
Are you crazy? We own those two. Look at them!
你疯了吗？他们任我们宰割

126
00:07:41,990 --> 00:07:44,960
He can't even breathe, and she's popping pills.
你看他们 他喘不过气来，她在吃药

127
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,750
You're not giving them a chance.
你根本不给他们机会 

128
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,450
They have rackets.
他们有球拍不是吗？

129
00:07:52,970 --> 00:07:54,760
We'll make this the last game.
宾，我想打完这场就收了

130
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,970
Yes,sir. Put me out of my misery.
沤猓我求之不得 

131
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,230
Are you sure you never played pro?
你真的没打过职业？

132
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,000
Please let them win.
拜托让他们赢

133
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:04,970
I'll take it down to 95%, but that's the best I can do.
我顶多只能把战力降到95%

134
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,680
-Missed it! -I got it!
糟糕，漏掉了 我来

135
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,510
Nice shot.
好球

136
00:08:27,030 --> 00:08:28,520
I got it!
我来

137
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,160
Long!
出界

138
00:08:37,610 --> 00:08:39,840
I can't believe you let them win.
你居然让他们赢

139
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:42,950
Well,at least you hid your feelings well about it.
至少你把不爽掩饰得很好

140
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:44,710
I was frustrated.
我很沮丧

141
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:45,910
It's my racket.
这是我的球拍 

142
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,310
Frustrated with you!
是你让我沮丧

143
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:52,150
If we hadn't lost,they would never have invited us to dinner tomorrow.
如果没输那场球 他们也不会找我们明天去吃饭

144
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,420
What bothers me...
我最困扰的是 

145
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:56,060
...is how different you act around them.
你在他们身边整个人都变了

146
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:59,200
The throwing the tennis games, the fake laugh...
故意输球，工作笑

147
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,960
...the "See you later,Bing!" "Not if I see you first,Doug!"
“回头见，宾” “不回头就不见”

148
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:07,770
Listen,I don't sound like some crazed, drunken pirate.
我哪有笑得像喝醉的海盗

149
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:11,530
I know you don't, but "work Chandler" does.
你没有，但工作的钱德有

150
00:09:11,710 --> 00:09:14,440
I don't like work Chandler. The guy's a suck-up.
我不喜欢工作的钱德 那家伙是个狗腿

151
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:17,120
Because you said that...
因为你这些话 
152
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,180
...I'm not putting out tonight!
我晚上不跟你玩了


153
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:29,620
Something's wrong. My brother doesn't stay out all night.
绝对有问题 我哥从来不彻夜不归

154
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,990
Maybe we should check the trash chute.
也许应该去看看垃圾槽

155
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:35,970
Ross couldn't fit down the trash chute.
罗斯挤不进垃圾槽

156
00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:38,400
That's right. He almost could.
没错，就差那么一点点

157
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:41,140
Which is exactly how I got stuck there.
所以我之前卡住过

158
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,870
Oh,my God!
他回来了 天哪

159
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:48,240
Where the hell have you been?
你死哪去了？

160
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:51,350
Just,you know,out.
就是去外面了

161
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:56,080
Oh,out! God,I don't know why we didn't think to check there.
外面，天哪 我们怎么没去那里找

162
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,820
What were you doing?
你都在做什么？

163
00:09:58,030 --> 00:10:00,860
I went to a bar,and then...
我先去喝酒，然后...

164
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:04,430
...I just walked around for a while.
...就随便走了走

165
00:10:04,730 --> 00:10:07,900
You walked around all night in the city by yourself?
你整夜一个人在外面乱晃？

166
00:10:09,670 --> 00:10:10,900
He hooked up!
他嘿咻了

167
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:14,200
He hooked up.
他跟某人嘿咻了

168
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:17,610
I don't have to answer your questions. I'm a big boy.
我不必回答你们的问题 我是个大人

170
00:10:17,850 --> 00:10:19,180
I can do what I want.
爱怎样就怎样

171
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:20,680
He hooked up!
他嘿咻了

172
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,870
Tell us about her!
聊聊她嘛

173
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:27,120
Ross,you left your scarf
罗斯，你把围巾掉在…

174
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,960
Hey,you guys.
你们好

176
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:46,510
I know what you all are thinking, but Chandler is in Yemen.
好，我知道你们在想什么 但钱德在叶门

178
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:51,510
I'm a young woman. I have needs. I can't wait forever.
我还年轻，我有需求 我不能等一辈子

179
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,810
Yeah,that's what I was thinking.
我也是这么想的

180
00:10:55,850 --> 00:11:00,150
So I'm asking you,please, just take a moment before you judge me.
所以我求求你们 在批评我之前先想一下

181
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,720
Nobody's judging you.
没有人在批评你

182
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:07,690
Mr. Right-place-at-the-right-time...
你，天时地利人和先生

183
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:11,200
...call me.
跟我联络

184
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:21,400
So I guess you finished your book.
看来你的书看完了

185
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:25,480
Had some time on our hands,did we?
有点闲是吧？

186
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:29,710
I know what you guys are going to say.
我知道你们要说什么…

187
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,550
You two would have very hairy children.
你们的孩子会毛茸茸的

188
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:36,150
I didn't know you'd say that.
我不知道你会说那个

189
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:39,160
Ross! Janice?
罗斯，珍妮丝耶？

190
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,290
All right. Hold on,hold on.
等一下… 

191
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,330
This is Ross.
这是罗斯

192
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,660
He's our friend. He obviously went crazy.
他是我们的朋友 他显然是疯了

193
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:48,930
He obviously lost his mind.
脑筋秀逗了

194
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:54,700
Look,it's not that crazy. Okay?
没那么夸张，好吗？ 

195
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,810
But it's Janice! I mean,she's...
但是珍妮丝耶 她是…

196
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:59,880
...Janice!
...珍妮丝耶

197
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:02,410
How drunk were you?
你醉得太离谱了

198
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:04,740
Janice and I have a lot in common.
珍妮丝和我有很多共同点

199
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:09,050
We've both been divorced. We both have kids.
我们都离过婚，我们都有小孩

200
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:11,190
Are you going to see her again?
你真的要再见她？ 

201
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:14,190
-Don't put ideas in his head! -I will see her.
菲比，别影响他 我确实要再见她 

202
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,420
Damn it,Phoebe!
你看啦

203
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:23,800
I have to tell you something that I've never admitted.
我要说出一件我没坦承过的事 

204
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:28,240
In high school,I made out with James even though I knew you liked him.
高中时 我知道你喜欢詹姆法洛 但还是跟他上了床

206
00:12:28,510 --> 00:12:31,710
That feels so good to get off my chest. Okay,you go.
哇，说出来的感觉真好 好，该你了

207
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:35,810
My turn? What are you talking about?
该我了？什么意思？

209
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:40,220
I know about you and Chandler.
摩妮卡，我知道你和钱德的事

210
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:44,990
I overheard you on the phone the other day.
什么？ 我那天听到你们在讲电话

211
00:12:45,230 --> 00:12:49,420
You said, "I'll tell Rachel I'm doing laundry for a couple of hours."
你说“我会告诉瑞秋” “我要花两个小时洗衣服”

212
00:12:49,660 --> 00:12:52,600
And he said, "Laundry? Is that my new nickname?"
他说“洗衣服？” “那是我的新绰号吗？”

213
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:54,730
And you said:
然后你说

214
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:58,930
"You know what your nickname is, Mr. Big."
“不是” “你明知你的绰号是大雕”

215
00:13:04,610 --> 00:13:07,550
You're writing yourself a little play there,Rach.
原来你正在写剧本 

216
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:12,110
Let me know how it turns out.
记得把结局告诉我

217
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:16,890
I wouldn't know,because I got so freaked out I hung up the phone.
我不知道 因为我吓到把电话挂掉了

218
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:19,520
Well,if you had kept listening...
如果你听完 

219
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:23,360
...you would have heard me call him Mister...
你会听到我是叫他大…

220
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:24,520
...Bigot.
碉堡

221
00:13:25,730 --> 00:13:27,430
Mr. Bigot.
什么？ 大碉堡

222
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:32,470
He tells the most racist jokes.
他喜欢讲碉堡的笑话

223
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:35,970
All right. So that's it.
好，所以就这样 

224
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,870
There's nothing going on between you and Chandler?
你是说你和钱德之间没什么

225
00:13:40,210 --> 00:13:42,410
Me and Chandler?
我和钱德？

226
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:48,420
Put your $20 down.
拿出20元来

227
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:51,590
First one to find the tasty treat wins,okay?
先找到零食的赢，好吗？

228
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:56,150
All right,let's get the contestants out of their isolation booths.
好，请参赛者从休息室出场

229
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,790
And they're off!
它们出场了

230
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,660
Get your foot off my contestant! Judge?
别挡住我的参赛者，裁判

231
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:04,840
Judge rules,no violation.
裁判判定没有违规

232
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,168
你们好

233
00:14:10,010 --> 00:14:14,280
It's so weird to say this, but I just had a great date with Janice.
说也奇怪 我今天跟珍妮丝过得很开心

234
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,780
-What? -Are you serious?
什么？ 真的假的？

235
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:20,950
I opened up to her about all the stuff that's been happening to me.
没错，我跟她诉说近来的惨事 

236
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,020
I mean,I talked for hours.
我说了好几个小时

237
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:24,420
It is amazing...
这种感觉真好

238
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:28,150
...to have someone give you such focused attention.
有人能专心听你倾诉

239
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:31,330
You don't need Janice for that. You've got us.
那你何必找她，你有我们

240
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:33,330
The duck gets the Nutter Butter!
鸭子找到花生酱饼干了 不

241
00:14:34,770 --> 00:14:37,500
That's not a Nutter Butter. That's an old won ton!
那不是花生酱饼干 那是一颗馄饨

242
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:39,000
Judge rules...
裁判判定：

243
00:14:39,310 --> 00:14:40,800
...Nutter Butter.
是花生酱饼干

244
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:42,980
Tough call.
真难判 是啊

245
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:51,950
Seriously,I strongly believe that we should support President Clinton...
但我们应该支持柯林顿总统 

246
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,350
...and her husband,Bill.
和她的老公比尔

247
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:58,890
How do you like your coffee?
你们的咖啡要怎么上？

248
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,060
-None for me. -A little sugar.
我不要，谢谢 我要一点点糖

249
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:04,860
I'll have Monica stick her finger in it. That will sweeten it up.
那就让摩妮卡把指头伸进去 应该就会甜了

250
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:12,340
-That laugh doesn't give you a headache? -You get used to it.
你那样笑怎么不会头痛？ 久了就习惯了

251
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:13,970
I don't think that I can.
我不觉得我会习惯 

252
00:15:14,210 --> 00:15:16,680
This will be it for me on the work things.
我以后就不甩这套了

253
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:19,310
I laugh at my boss's jokes. What's the big deal?
老板说笑我就笑，这有什么吗

254
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:22,040
I'd rather not be with this work-weasel guy...
我干嘛要陪一个没尊严的马屁精

255
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:25,480
...when I can be with my boyfriend, who I actually respect.
如果能跟我尊敬的男友在一起 

256
00:15:29,890 --> 00:15:34,350
I got to apologize for Kara's coffee. I'd feel sorry for it in a fight.
我得为卡拉煮的咖啡道歉 如果它去打架 

258
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:37,360
It's not strong enough to defend itself.
连自己都保护不了

259
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,830
Hear what I said?
你听到我的话了吗？ 

260
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,030
What?
什么？

261
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:48,310
It's a joke. What's the matter with you?
那个笑话啊，你是怎么了？

262
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:51,570
Well,I just didn't think it was funny,sir.
我只是觉得不好笑

263
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:52,840
Excuse me?
你说什么？

264
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:56,340
-Well,I just -Honey?
我只是… 亲爱的

265
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:59,020
I just don't think you understood the joke.
我觉得你没听懂

266
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:01,010
Really?
是吗？ 

267
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:05,120
I mean,it was really funny. I just don't think that you got it.
很好笑耶，你一定是没听懂

269
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:08,860
You see,Kara's coffee is weak-tasting.
卡拉煮的咖啡很稀

270
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:13,120
But what Doug did was imply that it was weak physically.
但道格是在暗示它很虚弱

271
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:18,430
-You get it now,honey? -I think I do!
现在你懂了吗？ 我懂了

272
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:25,640
-Thank you,Monica. -I thought you could use the help.
谢谢你 我觉得你需要解释

273
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:28,940
Coffee in a fight!
咖啡打架

274
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:36,880
You mind if I read my comic books in here?
瑞秋，我可以在这里看漫画吗

275
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:41,350
Sure. Why?
当然可以，怎么了？

276
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:45,720
Chandler and Monica are over there. It's kind of hard to concentrate.
钱德和摩妮卡在一起 我很难专心

277
00:16:46,770 --> 00:16:50,330
She just called and said she was going to be working late.
什么？她刚打来说她要加班

278
00:16:50,570 --> 00:16:52,300
She keeps lying to me.
她一直骗我 

279
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:56,570
That's it! I'm going over there and confronting them right now.
够了，我现在就过去揭穿他们

280
00:16:59,250 --> 00:17:01,010
Panty raid.
去找小裤裤！

281
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:16,120
All right,so you're telling me that I have to tell racist jokes now?
所以我得讲碉堡的笑话？

282
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:19,200
I'm just not very good at this.
对不起，我不太会圆谎

283
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:22,230
I'm a terrible liar. I hate having to lie to Rachel.
我很不会骗人 我又很讨厌骗瑞秋

284
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:25,200
-But we're not ready to tell yet. -I know.
但我们还不能公开 我知道，只是…

285
00:17:25,410 --> 00:17:30,110
Ever since high school, Rachel was the one person that I told everything to.
从高中起我什么事都告诉瑞秋

286
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:32,400
I miss that so much now.
我好怀念那种感觉 

287
00:17:32,610 --> 00:17:34,710
She's my best friend.
她是我最要好的朋友

288
00:17:41,927 --> 00:17:42,985
乔伊？

289
00:17:44,090 --> 00:17:45,620
Oh,my God,Rachel!
天哪，瑞秋

290
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:51,060
What are you doing here?
你怎么跑来这里？

291
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:56,630
Well,I actually came over here to borrow this lamp...
我是…我来借这盏灯 

292
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,400
...to look at my books.
好看书...

293
00:17:59,670 --> 00:18:01,640
You know,see them a little better.
看得清楚一点

294
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:05,400
Okay,great.
太好了

295
00:18:06,610 --> 00:18:09,980
Well,what I was doing in Chandler's room is that...
我在钱德的房间里是因为… 

296
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:11,480
...I was cleaning it.
我在帮忙打扫

297
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:14,680
He pays me to clean it.
他付钱请我打扫

298
00:18:15,820 --> 00:18:19,090
What a great way to make some extra pocket money.
真是个赚零用钱的好办法

299
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:23,690
When I said to you earlier that I was at work...
之前我说要加班 

300
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,630
...I'm at my new work.
...是指我的新工作

301
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:28,600
Good enough. Right?
真不错，对吧？

303
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:34,000
I'll go look at my books.
好，那…我要去看书了

304
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,540
Go get back to my new job.
好，我得去忙我的新工作了

305
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:41,819
好

306
00:18:44,650 --> 00:18:47,020
Congratulations on your new job!
恭喜你找到这份工作

307
00:18:54,030 --> 00:18:56,220
Man,she is really gullible.
天哪，她可真好骗

308
00:19:02,370 --> 00:19:04,530
-Here you go. -Thanks.
你们的咖啡 谢谢

309
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:07,300
-Actually,I should get going. -You're sure?
其实我该走了 你确定？ 

310
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:09,670
I can stay out as late as you want.
你想留多晚我都奉陪

311
00:19:09,910 --> 00:19:12,070
I told you I'm on sabbatical from work
我说过我为什么休长假吧？ 

312
00:19:12,310 --> 00:19:14,800
Yes,yes. You did.
对，你说过

313
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:17,750
-Oh,man! -What is wrong now?
又怎么了？

314
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:20,850
This isn't what I ordered.
我不是点的这个

315
00:19:21,050 --> 00:19:25,220
Man! Can't anything go right in my life?
我的人生就不能顺利一点吗？

316
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:28,990
First,my marriage falls apart, and then
先是我的婚姻破裂，然后…

317
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,250
I know!
我知道！

318
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,090
You lose your apartment, you lose your job...
然后你被赶出你家 你的工作没了

319
00:19:33,370 --> 00:19:37,330
...your ex-wife gets married so fast! And now the coffee!
你的前妻很快就再婚 现在咖啡又错了

320
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:42,100
-We need to talk. -Okay.
我们得谈一谈 好

321
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:46,410
-Sometimes I feel -No,no,don't.
有时我觉得… 不…

322
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,610
I'm going to talk.
是我要说

323
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,920
I believe...
我认为 

324
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,020
...that the sun has set...
我们的美好时光

325
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:57,420
...on our day in the sun.
已经日落了

326
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:03,390
You're a very sweet person,Ross.
什么？ 你是个很好的人

327
00:20:06,130 --> 00:20:07,430
Unfortunately...
只是...

328
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:11,760
...I just don't think I can take another second of you whining!
我没办法再听你哀下去了

329
00:20:14,780 --> 00:20:18,210
Let me make sure I'm hearing this right.
我跟你确认一下

330
00:20:19,310 --> 00:20:22,810
You're ending this with me because...
你要跟我结束 因为...

331
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:24,570
...I'm too whiny?
...我太会发牢骚？

332
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,780
So you're saying...
你是说

333
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:33,220
...I've become so whiny...
...我是这么地爱发牢骚...

334
00:20:33,490 --> 00:20:35,120
...that l...
...我...

335
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,990
...annoy you...
...让你觉得很烦...

336
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:40,890
...Janice.
...珍妮丝…

337
00:20:41,170 --> 00:20:42,430
Well,yeah!
没错 

338
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:45,230
Oh,my God!
我…的…天哪

339
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:49,230
Will you be okay?
你不要紧吧？ 

340
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,140
I am now.
现在不要紧了

341
00:21:03,290 --> 00:21:05,320
I guess that's two out of three...
已经两人出局了…

342
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:07,620
...Joey!
...乔伊

343
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:19,360
-Dude,we got to talk. -Okay.
我们得谈一谈 好

344
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:24,370
I wanted to tell you something before you heard it from someone else.
我只是想趁你听说之前告诉你

345
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:27,510
I hope this isn't too weird,but...
希望不会太奇怪

346
00:21:29,020 --> 00:21:31,610
...I had a thing with Janice.
我最近跟珍妮丝交往过

347
00:21:36,460 --> 00:21:37,920
You're not mad?
你不生气？ 

348
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,320
Why would I be mad?
我干嘛生气？

349
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:42,720
Because there's certain rules about this kind of stuff.
因为这种事有它的道义在

350
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:46,660
You don't fool around with your friends' ex-girlfriends...
不能追朋友的旧情人

351
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:51,300
...or possible girlfriends or girls they're related to.
心上人 或是有亲属关系的人

352
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:58,230
I am mad.
我很生气

353
00:22:00,010 --> 00:22:02,480
But you know, I'm going to forgive you.
但是你知道吗？我要原谅你

354
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:04,710
Because that's what friends do.
因为那样才叫兄弟

355
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:09,180
They forgive their friends when they do everything you just said.
他们会原谅朋友 犯了你念的那串禁忌

356
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:10,690
Thank you.
谢谢

357
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,590
But I want you to remember...
不过我要你记住...

358
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:15,190
...that I forgave you.
...我原谅了你

359
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:21,660
I also want you to remember that I let you live here rent-free.
好 我还要你记住我免费收留你

360
00:22:22,170 --> 00:22:23,360
All right.
好 

361
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:27,200
And I want you to remember that I gave you...
我还要你记住我送你...

362
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:29,240
...twenty-seven dollars.
...27块钱

363
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:31,870
No strings attached!
无条件奉送

364
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:33,440
If you can't remember that...
要是你记不住 

365
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:36,340
